<p>
  <h2>Academic Background</h2></p>
  <p><b>Master of Business Administration (MBA), Yale School of Management, Yale University (2017 Expected)</b></p>

<p>I am currently an MBA candidate at the Yale School of Management. Please go to the MBA at Yale page to learn more about my experiences. [button] </p>

<p><b>Bachelor of Business Administration (BBA) – Finance, McCombs School of Business, The University of Texas at Austin (2010) </p>

<p>Bachelor of Arts – Economics, Art History (minor), UT College of Liberal Arts, The University of Texas at Austin (2010) – Distinguished College Scholar </b></p>

<img src="file:///Users/gsussman/Dropbox/dhruthi%20website/230523_504387104065_6923_n.jpg" class="img-responsive rounded-image" alt="Cinque Terre"  style="max-height:327px; float: right; padding-left: 10px;">

<p>My extracurricular focus at UT was serving as the President of the Blanton Student Guild, a student organization that managed the relationship between Jack S. Blanton Museum of Art and UT. I strategized methods for the museum to draw more students into the museum including museum certification, director search committee, and hosting 6 mixers totaling $45k and 5k attendees. In the fall of 2009, I left my presidency to intern as the first Undergraduate Finance Intern at The Metropolitan Museum of Art in New York. At The Met I consolidated financials and created a donor database for the CFO and CIO to project future cash flows.</p>

<p>
  <h2>Awards/Honors</h2></p>

<p>Accenture USA Corporate Citizenship Volunteer Award (2014) - One of ten national finalist selected. Awarded for invention Request for Proposal Job Shadow Program and leading 7 sessions adding 200 students and 420 volunteer hours toward national Corporate Citizenship goals.</p>

<p>The University of Texas at Austin Distinguished College Scholar (2010) – Awarded for ranking in the top 4% of class</p>

